Q6.6: Yes. I believe the Pilot study (on paper) was acting as a mental "primer" to the computer test. The written questions asked were generally under the assumption that your relationship was a positive one. Asking such questions that included, "being upset if the relationship ended" or "Reasons why it would be nice to grow old with your partner" are extremely biased. If one who answered these questions and their current relationship status was a negative one (ie. my past relationship) their answers would reflect a different outlook. Study participants might have a difficult time trying to answer the questions with a positive answer when their true honest response would be negative. Going into the computer test, the available answers in the hypothetical scenarios, there was always at least one "negative" response to the action. Such as "getting revenge on my partner".
